race.description: P Mcgovern Principal Inglis Xtra Midway Mdn Plt
race.comment: FULLALOVE (9) ran on strongly as favourite first up over 900m at Newcastle, narrowly beaten. Had come off Stakes grade and the longer sprint suits now. In the right race and is sure to prove hard to beat. EVERYBODY RISE (1) is third-up and has plenty up his sleeve. The speed-bred gelding draws wide but rates to make the finish with average luck in the run. COSMONAUT (5) went close at Newcastle first-up and then was never in contention at Rosehill at long odds. Has the blinkers on for the first time and is better suited. Has the rail and more to give. MAMMA MIA (13) was only beaten 2.2L here on debut and it was a tough effort. Draws out but fitter she will be hitting the line hard. CHEEKY SORT (12) went close as favourite here on debut and the local has claims if she takes her place.
